<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-10T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-10T05:00:00-05:00" n="762" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/74: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-10T13:00:00+03:00">April 10,
                                1941—1 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>726. The Chinese Ambassador<note n="43" xml:id="d762fn43">Shao Li-tzu.</note>
                        told me last night that he had seen Lozovski<note n="44" xml:id="d762fn44">Soviet Assistant Commissar for Foreign Affairs.</note> “several times
                        recently” and that the latter had emphasized that if Japan wished a
                        non-aggression pact with the Soviet Union “it would be very difficult [”]
                        for the Soviet Union to refuse.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>